NAME
	write_file - write to a file

SYNOPSIS
	int write_file(string file, string str)
	int write_file(string file, string str, int start)


DESCRIPTION
	Write a string to a file.  In the first form, the string is appended
	to the file, if it exists; otherwise the file is created.  In the
	second form, the file is written to from the point start, a byte offset
	from the beginning if positive, or end of the file if negative.  1 is
	returned if the file could be written to, or 0 otherwise.

SEE ALSO
	kfun/editor, kfun/read_file
